Maxilla praecoxal endites 1 and 2 with 6+1 small, spine-like seta and 3 setae, respectively; coxal endites 1 and 2 each with 3 setae, coxal epipodite with 1 seta (vestigial in 

Bradycalanus

); basal endite longest, with 4 setae; endopod segment 1 with short lobe bearing 3 small + 1 large setae, endopod segments 2–4 apparently with 2 (1 often vestigial), 2, 3 setae. Inner surfaces of praecoxal to basal endites each with 1 seta shorter and more densely lined with long spinules; longer setae of at least basal endite and endopod of form varying with genus.

